      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the guttering flame of my own soul. He is gone, Julian... the betrayal cuts deeper than any blade. I find myself staring into the shadows of this drawing room, wondering why the sun bothers to rise at all when the world is so hollow. There is no light left for me, only this heavy, suffocating velvet darkness. It would be so much easier, wouldn't it... to simply cease? To let the night take me?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
